 not available to the public, yet it is a popular tourist site. The original court is also visible within a complex within this tower. The Raj Niwas' major draw is its monolithic pillars, which were transferred here from the Gingee Fort in 1751. Aside from that, several Gingee Fort pillars surround the Gandhi Mandapam on Promenade Beach. 13. Botanical Garden in Pondicherry The Botanical Garden, also known as C.S. Perrotate, is a famous tourist site in Pondicherry. It was founded in 1862. As the name suggests, this garden is a fish house with various exotic plants. Tourists may witness flora collected from various areas of India and worldwide. This aquarium is a fantastic spot to observe a variety of aquatic species as well as some beautiful fish. If planning a trip to Pondicherry, you must include the Botanical Garden in your schedule. 14. Chidambram in Pondicherry Chidambaram is a lovely temple town 63 kilometres from Pondicherry, known for the Lord Nataraja temple and the famed chariot festival. Chidambaram is located 250 kilometres from Chennai, a place of religious significance since ancient times. Because of different cultural influences, the city has a rich legacy and customs. Many dynasties ruled here, including Vijayanagar emperors, the Cholas, Marathas, Pandyas, and the British. Chidambaram is well-known for its many temples. If visiting Pondicherry, you should travel to Chidambaram to see the temples. 15. Water Sports in Pondicherry Pondicherry is a beach lover's dream. Tourists are drawn to the area's beautiful beaches. Sunbathing on the beaches here is a lovely experience for everyone. Pondicherry's beaches are also well-known for water sports. Water sports such as parasailing, scuba diving, and banana boat excursions are available to visitors. How to Reach Pondicherry Pondicherry is in South India and is well connected by air to the rest of the country and most major cities worldwide. Aside from that, it has excellent rail and road connections to all of India's main cities. 1. By Flight If travelling to Pondicherry, you should know that the primary airport is Pondicherry Airport. You can use cabs or taxis to get to the city from the airport. Another alternative is to take a flight from the Karaikal airport. 2. By Train Villupuram Railway Junction is Pondicherry's principal railway station, connecting it to key towns around India. 3. By Bus A road trip to Pondicherry may provide an intense experience. There are several significant cities to visit here, including Trichy, Chennai, Bangalore, and Coimbatore. Local Food in Pondicherry Pondicherry is one of the Indian cities where French food has impacted the food. Several eateries serve French cuisine in this area. Baguettes, Italian Baked Beans, Croissants, Stuffed Cabbage, and many more dishes are popular here. In addition, foods from other South Indian states may be sampled in this union region. La Cafe Carte Blanche, Maison Rose, Satsang, Cafe de Flor, Well Cafe, and Le Cafe are some of the most well-known restaurants in Pondicherry. Best Time to Visit Pondicherry If you want to visit Pondicherry, the ideal time is between October and March. During this period, the temperature in the city ranges from 15 to 30 degrees Celsius. The summers here are fairly hot, with temperatures reaching 40 degrees Celsius. The monsoon season is also a fantastic time to visit. However, the optimal time to visit Pondicherry differs from person to person because this city varies with the seasons and has several events that are popular with travellers. Next TopicTourist Places in Chennai ? prev next ? For Videos Join Our Youtube Channel: Join Now Feedback Send your Feedback to [email protected] Help Others, Please Share Learn Latest Tutorials Splunk SPSS Swagger Transact-SQL Tumblr ReactJS Regex Reinforcement Learning R Programming RxJS React Native Python Design Patterns Python Pillow Python Turtle Keras Preparation Aptitude Reasoning Verbal Ability Interview Questions Company Questions